{"threadId": "14b84866348901dd", "messages": [
{"messageId": "14b84866348901dd", "headers": {"From": "Jim Rutt <jimrutt@gmail.com>", "Date": "Fri, 13 Feb 2015 11:59:33 -0800", "Subject": "[opencog-dev] cog-get-pred examples or documentation?"}, "body": "The cog-get-pred scheme procedure sounds useful but the description doesn't provide much on how to use it."},
{"messageId": "14b84c5b16bc7a27", "headers": {"From": "Linas Vepstas <linasvepstas@gmail.com>", "Date": "Fri, 13 Feb 2015 15:08:20 -0600", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] cog-get-pred examples or documentation?"}, "body": "I just pushed a fix enabling documentation for all functions in utilities.scm. cog-get-pred returns a list of predicates of the given type that an instance participates in via EvaluationLinks."},
{"messageId": "14b97f4fa0341004", "headers": {"From": "Jim Rutt <jim@jimrutt.com>", "Date": "Tue, 17 Feb 2015 09:33:06 -0500", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] cog-get-pred examples or documentation?"}, "body": "Docs are helpful, but calling them up from the guile prompt doesn't seem to work, I get a syntax error."},
{"messageId": "14b9807e14de6dbd", "headers": {"From": "Jim Rutt <jim@jimrutt.com>", "Date": "Tue, 17 Feb 2015 09:53:45 -0500", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] cog-get-pred examples or documentation?"}, "body": "Also, the documentation isn't quite clear enough. cog-get-pred with a specific PredicateNode returns an empty list."},
{"messageId": "14b993e44e6d5e19", "headers": {"From": "Linas Vepstas <linasvepstas@gmail.com>", "Date": "Tue, 17 Feb 2015 14:32:27 -0600", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] cog-get-pred examples or documentation?"}, "body": "The shell at port 17001 does not support the meta-commands, such as ,describe. You would have to use either the repl shell at 18001 or use guile directly."},
{"messageId": "14b9950d375f60af", "headers": {"From": "Linas Vepstas <linasvepstas@gmail.com>", "Date": "Tue, 17 Feb 2015 14:52:43 -0600", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] cog-get-pred examples or documentation?"}, "body": "The intended use is: (cog-get-pred (ConceptNode \"Dog\") 'PredicateNode). Most utilities are very short, typically 5-10 lines of code, and documentation tends to exceed the code length."},
{"messageId": "14b995981113f3e4", "headers": {"From": "Jim Rutt <jim@jimrutt.com>", "Date": "Tue, 17 Feb 2015 16:02:30 -0500", "Subject": "Re: [opencog-dev] cog-get-pred examples or documentation?"}, "body": "Ok, that worked. Close to enough to what I need at this time."}
]}
